{"lemma":"حُرْماتُ","slug":"حُرْماتُ","root":"ح.ر.م","root_slug":"ح-ر-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ر-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حُرْمَة","root":"حرم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":20},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7754","n7764","n7765","n7766","n7767","n7768"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَرُمَ (ḥaruma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inviolateness, prohibition, unlawfulness; something forbidden, something outlawed, something banned, something restricted, a taboo"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inviolateness, prohibition, unlawfulness; something inviolable, something that would bring dishonor or disgrace if violated or infringed"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"holiness, sanctity, sacredness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"holiness, sanctity, sacredness; something sacred, something that must be respected or honored"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an entitlement; something morally required, a moral right, an obligation; an agreement, a contract, a pact, a compact"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an entitlement; something morally required, a moral right, an obligation; a portion, a share"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an entitlement; something morally required, a moral right, an obligation; the right of clientship"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an entitlement; something morally required, a moral right, an obligation; the right of companionship, the right of friendship"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"honor, dignity; respect, reverence; veneration; a man's good name, a man's standing, a man's stature, a man's repute"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"honor, dignity; respect, reverence; veneration; a man's personal or private affairs","tags":["broadly"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"honor, dignity; respect, reverence; veneration; the persons whom the master of the house is responsible for or is in charge of, a man's household; a man's female family members, a man's wife, a man's daughter","examples":[{"text":"وَحُرْمَةُ الرَّجُلِ: حُرَمُهُ وَأَهْلُهُ. وَحَرَمُ الرَّجُلِ وَحَرِيمُهُ: مَا يُقَاتِلُ عَنْهُ وَيَحْمِيهُ، فَجَمْعُ الْحَرَمِ أَحْرَامٌ، وَجَمْعُ الْحَرِيِمِ حُرُمٌ.","english":"And a man's ḥurmah is his dignity [literally \"his affairs that must be respected\"] and his family, and his ḥaram and his ḥarīm are what he fights for and protects. And the plural of ḥaram is ʾaḥrām, and that of ḥarīm is ḥurum."},{"text":"حُرَمُكَ: نِسَاؤُكَ وَمَا تَحْمِي، وَهِيَ الْمَحَارِِمُ، اَلْوَاحِدَةُ: مَحْرُمَةٌ","english":"Your ḥuram are your women and what you protect, also called maḥārim. Its singular is maḥrumah."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"honor, dignity; respect, reverence; veneration; a man's honor when related to the demeanor, conduct, reputation, or treatment of his female relations","tags":["broadly"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"honor, dignity; respect, reverence; veneration; a woman's honor, chastity, purity, maidenhood, virginity, maidenhead, virtue"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"honor, dignity; respect, reverence; veneration; a woman's reputation of being decent or modest"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"honor, dignity; respect, reverence; veneration; a woman's personal or private affairs","tags":["broadly"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shelter, protection","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَرُمَ (ḥaruma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rut"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"deception"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7754","headword_ar":"حرّمهُ","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHoriymN","text_ar":"تَحْرِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) said of God, (K,) and of a man, (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He forbade it, prohibited it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it unlawful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, *)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHrmhu","text_ar":"احرمهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHoraAmN","text_ar":"اـِحْرَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) The saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hu A^akobaru","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُ اَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"at the commencement of prayer is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takobiyrapu Alt~aHoriymi","text_ar":"تَكْبِيرَةُ التَّحْرِيمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkbyrp","text_ar":"تكبيرة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of prohibition"},{"kind":"text","text":"], because it prohibits the person praying from saying and doing anything extraneous to prayer: and it is also termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkbyrpu AlA_iHoraAmi","text_ar":"تكبيرةُ الاـِحْرَامِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkbyrp","text_ar":"تكبيرة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of entering upon a state of prohibition"},{"kind":"text","text":"by prayer. (TA.) It is said in a trad., of Ibn- 'Abbás,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA Har~ama Alr~ajulu A@moraA^atahu fahiYa yamiynN yukaf~iruhaA","text_ar":"اـِذَا حَرَّمَ الرَّجُلُ ا@مْرَاَتَهُ فَهِىَ يَمِينٌ يُكَفِّرُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the man declares his wife to be forbidden to him, it is an oath, which he must expiate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHoriym","text_ar":"تَحْرِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a wife and of a female slave may be without the intention of divorce. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~amotu AlZ~uloma EalaY nafosiY","text_ar":"حَرَّمْتُ الظُّلْمَ عَلَى نَفْسِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in another trad., [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have forbidden myself wrongdoing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"said by Mohammad,] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am far above wrongdoing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHoriymN","text_ar":"تَحْرِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hur~imN","text_ar":"حُرِّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being refractory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"untractable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though forbidden to the rider;] whence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHar~amN","text_ar":"مُحَرَّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] applied to a camel. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pronounced, it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him, sacred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inviolable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entitled to reverence"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuHar~amu","text_ar":"المُحَرَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haram","text_ar":"حَرَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Mekkeh, &c:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, made him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to be reverenced, respected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honoured."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound it hard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a whip. (KL.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He tanned it incompletely"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that it became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remained, hard"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; namely, a hide. (KL.)       -A3-  See also 4, in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n7764","headword_ar":"حُرْمَةٌ","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of being forbidden, prohibited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unlawful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of being sacred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inviolable; sacredness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inviolability:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haruma","text_ar":"حَرُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which it is an inf. n.:)] and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of being revered, respected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honoured."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoramN","text_ar":"مَحْرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also, (Az, Mgh, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HurumapN","text_ar":"حُرُمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuramapN","text_ar":"حُرَمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Reverence, respect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, K, TK;) a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiHotiraAmN","text_ar":"اِحْتِرَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furoqapN","text_ar":"فُرْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifotiraAqN","text_ar":"اِفْتِرَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoramN","text_ar":"مَحْرَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; but properly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huromap","text_ar":"حُرْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) pl. of the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuramaAtN","text_ar":"حُرَمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HurumaAtN","text_ar":"حُرُمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromaAtN","text_ar":"حُرْمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"grfAt","text_ar":"غرفات"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurofapN","text_ar":"غُرْفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb) When a man has relationship [to us], and we regard him with bashfulness, we say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu HuromapN","text_ar":"لَهُ حُرْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Reverence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is due to him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is rendered to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Az, TA.) And we say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lilomusolimi EalaY","text_ar":"لِلْمُسْلِمِ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almusolimi HuromapN","text_ar":"المُسْلِمِ حُرْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Reverence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the Muslim is incumbent on the Muslim"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Az, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that should be sacred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inviolable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoramapN","text_ar":"مَحْرَمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHorumapN","text_ar":"مَحْرُمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoramN","text_ar":"مَحْرَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) as, for instance, a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reputation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing which one is under an obligation to reverence, respect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and defend"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Jel in ii. 190:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing of which one is under an obligation to be mindful, observant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regardful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd ibid.:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"everything that is entitled to reverence, respect, honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defence, in the character and appertenances"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a person:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that one is bound to do,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from which one is bound to refrain, from a motive of reverence, respect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see the next sentence:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any attribute that renders the subject thereof entitled to reverence, respect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromapN","text_ar":"حُرْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HurumaAtN","text_ar":"حُرُمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd and Jel ubi suprà, and TA) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuramaAtN","text_ar":"حُرَمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromaAtN","text_ar":"حُرْمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as above,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuramN","text_ar":"حُرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and that of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoramN","text_ar":"مَحْرَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoramapN","text_ar":"مَحْرَمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHorumapN","text_ar":"مَحْرُمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaArimu","text_ar":"مَحَارِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoramaAtN","text_ar":"مَحْرَمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHorumaAtN","text_ar":"مَحْرُمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[also] are pls. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoramapN","text_ar":"مَحْرَمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHorumapN","text_ar":"مَحْرُمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (As, S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HurumaAtu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"حُرُمَاتُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The inviolable ordinances and prohibitions of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ordinances of God, and other inviolable things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd and Jel * in xxii. 31:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what it is incumbent on one to perform, and unlawful to neglect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all the requisitions of God relating to the rites and ceremonies of the pilgrimage and to other things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh in xxii. 31:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haram","text_ar":"حَرَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sacred territory"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the requisitions relating to the pilgrimage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd ubi suprà:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the requisitions relating to the pilgrimage"},{"kind":"text","text":"in particular: (Ksh ubi suprà:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Kaabeh and the sacred mosque and the sacred territory and the sacred month and the person who is in the state of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHoraAm","text_ar":"اـِحْرَام"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ksh and Bd ibid.:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the inviolability"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huromap","text_ar":"حُرْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sacred territory and of the state of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHoraAm","text_ar":"اـِحْرَام"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of the sacred month:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mekkeh and the pilgrimage and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eumorap","text_ar":"عُمْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and all the acts of disobedience to God which He has forbidden:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mujáhid, TA:) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the acts of disobedience to God."},{"kind":"text","text":"('Atà, TA.) ―         -b4-  And [hence, because it should be regarded as sacred, or inviolable,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*im~apN","text_ar":"ذِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A compact,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covenant, or an obligation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as renders one responsible for the safety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safe-keeping, of a person"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the restoration of a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the payment of a sum of money, &c.;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by which one becomes in a state of security"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safety:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"responsibility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suretiship:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"security,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safety; security of life and property; protection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safeguard; a promise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an assurance, of security, safety, protection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safeguard; indemnity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an obligation, a duty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due, that should be regarded as sacred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inviolable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the nonobservance of which is blameable"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b5-  And [hence also] A man's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huram","text_ar":"حُرَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wives,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"women under covert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"family:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and [in like manner the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuramN","text_ar":"حُرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromN","text_ar":"حُرْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but correctly like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zufarN","text_ar":"زُفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wives,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"women"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"under covert"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K, TA,) and his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"household,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"family,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what he protects,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defends;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaArimu","text_ar":"مَحَارِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the sing. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHorumapN","text_ar":"مَحْرُمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoramapN","text_ar":"مَحْرَمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) and hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromapN","text_ar":"حُرْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied by the vulgar to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wife."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [In Har, p. 377, a man's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huromap","text_ar":"حُرْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to mean his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haram","text_ar":"حَرَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"and his family: and in p. 489, a man's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haram","text_ar":"حَرَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to mean his family and his wives and those whom he protects, or defends. See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HariymN","text_ar":"حَرِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b6-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A share, portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSiybN","text_ar":"نَصِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["KL","Az","Mgh","Msb","K","S","TK","Zj","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n7765","headword_ar":"حِرْمَةٌ","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaramapN","text_ar":"حَرَمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, S, K) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desire"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a female cloven-hoofed animal, (K,) or of a ewe, or she-goat, (S,) and of a she-wolf and of a bitch, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the male:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaramapN","text_ar":"حَرَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in ewes, or she-goats, is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabaEapN","text_ar":"ضَبَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in she-camels, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HinaA='N","text_ar":"حِنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in ewes. (S.) It is also used, in a trad., in relation to male human beings. (K.) It is said in a trad., respecting those whom the hour [of the resurrection] shall overtake,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuboEavu Ealayohimu AlHiromapu wa yusolabuwna","text_ar":"تُبْعَثُ عَلَيْهِمُ الحِرْمَةُ وَ يُسْلَبُونَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHayaA='a","text_ar":"الحَيَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Venereal desire"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be made to befall them, and they shall be bereft of shame"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Lh","S"]},{"entry_id":"n7766","headword_ar":"حَرَمَةٌ","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next precedes."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n7767","headword_ar":"حُرَمَةٌ","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromapN","text_ar":"حُرْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n7768","headword_ar":"حُرُمَةٌ","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromapN","text_ar":"حُرْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}